The paper deals with auction theory and mechanism design, which are central topics in game theory and algorithmic economics. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.EC (Economics and Computation) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves analyzing worst-case efficiency loss, which requires mathematical analysis and optimization, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory) possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with Bayesian auctions, which involve probabilistic reasoning and decision-making, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category as well.
